{
  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Implement CMS Preview Template Resolution\n\nConfigure the CMS preview functionality to correctly apply and render page templates that match the published version of the site.\n\nRequirements:\n- Investigate why preview mode is not loading the correct templates\n- Ensure preview mode uses the same template selection logic as the live site\n- Map CMS content types to their corresponding page templates\n- Verify template data bindings are working correctly in preview mode\n- Handle cases where template may not exist or content type is misconfigured\n- Test preview functionality across all content types and page templates\n- Ensure preview accurately reflects how the page will appear when published\n- Validate that template assets (CSS, JS) load correctly in preview mode\n\nEdge cases to consider:\n- New content types without assigned templates\n- Template changes that haven't been deployed yet\n- Nested or dynamic template components\n- Custom fields that may not render in preview",
  "title": "Fix CMS preview template resolution and rendering",
